{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"Religion is more than belief."},{"time":3640,"text":"It's power, and it's influence."},{"time":6480,"text":"And that influence affects all of us,"},{"time":9120,"text":"every day, regardless of your own belief."},{"time":13000,"text":"Despite the enormous influence\nof religion on the world today,"},{"time":17080,"text":"we hold them to a different standard\nof scrutiny and accountability"},{"time":20880,"text":"than any other sector of our society."},{"time":23960,"text":"For example, if there were\na multinational organization,"},{"time":28400,"text":"government or corporation today"},{"time":31480,"text":"that said no female\ncould be on a leadership board,"},{"time":35760,"text":"not one woman could have\na decision-making authority,"},{"time":39880,"text":"not one woman could handle\nany financial matter,"},{"time":43760,"text":"we would have outrage."},{"time":45160,"text":"There would be sanctions."},{"time":46840,"text":"And yet this is a common practice\nin almost every world religion today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52400,"text":"We accept things in our religious lives"},{"time":54840,"text":"that we do not accept\nin our secular lives,"},{"time":57960,"text":"and I know this because I've been\ndoing it for three decades."},{"time":62040,"text":"I was the type of girl that fought every\nform of gender discrimination growing up."},{"time":66560,"text":"I played pickup basketball games\nwith the boys and inserted myself."},{"time":70600,"text":"I said I was going to be the first\nfemale President of the United States."},{"time":74060,"text":"I have been fighting\nfor the Equal Rights Amendment,"},{"time":76520,"text":"which has been dead for 40 years."},{"time":79000,"text":"I'm the first woman\nin both sides of my family"},{"time":82160,"text":"to ever work outside the home\nand ever receive a higher education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86360,"text":"I never accepted being excluded\nbecause I was a woman,"},{"time":91200,"text":"except in my religion."},{"time":93400,"text":"Throughout all of that time,"},{"time":94800,"text":"I was a part of a very patriarchal\northodox Mormon religion."},{"time":99120,"text":"I grew up in an enormously\ntraditional family."},{"time":101920,"text":"I have eight siblings,\na stay-at-home mother."},{"time":104080,"text":"My father's actually\na religious leader in the community."},{"time":108160,"text":"And I grew up in a world believing\nthat my worth and my standing"},{"time":113040,"text":"was in keeping these rules\nthat I'd known my whole life."},{"time":117120,"text":"You get married a virgin,\nyou never drink alcohol,"},{"time":119960,"text":"you don't smoke, you always do service,"},{"time":122360,"text":"you're a good kid."},{"time":124360,"text":"Some of the rules we had were strict,"},{"time":127960,"text":"but you followed the rules\nbecause you loved the people"},{"time":130600,"text":"and you loved the religion\nand you believed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133280,"text":"Everything about Mormonism\ndetermined what you wore,"},{"time":136120,"text":"who you dated, who you married."},{"time":137651,"text":"It determined what underwear we wore."},{"time":141040,"text":"I was the kind of religious\nwhere everyone I know"},{"time":144120,"text":"donated 10 percent of everything\nthey earned to the church,"},{"time":147520,"text":"including myself."},{"time":148760,"text":"From paper routes and babysitting,\nI donated 10 percent."},{"time":152720,"text":"I was the kind of religious\nwhere I heard parents tell children"},{"time":155800,"text":"when they're leaving\non a two-year proselytizing mission"},{"time":159440,"text":"that they would rather have them die"},{"time":162000,"text":"than return home\nwithout honor, having sinned."},{"time":165240,"text":"I was the type and the kind of religious"},{"time":167720,"text":"where kids kill themselves\nevery single year"},{"time":171200,"text":"because they're terrified\nof coming out to our community as gay."},{"time":175560,"text":"But I was also the kind of religious"},{"time":177600,"text":"where it didn't matter\nwhere in the world I lived,"},{"time":180160,"text":"I had friendship,\ninstantaneous mutual aid."},{"time":183960,"text":"This was where I felt safe.\nThis is certainty and clarity about life."},{"time":188200,"text":"I had help raising my little daughter."},{"time":190480,"text":"So that's why I accepted without question\nthat only men can lead,"},{"time":195400,"text":"and I accepted without question"},{"time":197560,"text":"that women can't have the spiritual\nauthority of God on the Earth,"},{"time":200720,"text":"which we call the priesthood."},{"time":202160,"text":"And I allowed discrepancies between\nmen and women in operating budgets,"},{"time":206680,"text":"disciplinary councils,\nin decision-making capacities,"},{"time":210080,"text":"and I gave my religion a free pass"},{"time":213240,"text":"because I loved it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215120,"text":"Until I stopped,"},{"time":217120,"text":"and I realized that I had\nbeen allowing myself to be treated"},{"time":220760,"text":"as the support staff\nto the real work of men."},{"time":225680,"text":"And I faced this contradiction in myself,"},{"time":228080,"text":"and I joined with other activists\nin my community."},{"time":230840,"text":"We've been working very, very, very hard\nfor the last decade and more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235240,"text":"The first thing we did\nwas raise consciousness."},{"time":237478,"text":"You can't change what you can't see."},{"time":240000,"text":"We started podcasting,\nblogging, writing articles."},{"time":243240,"text":"I created lists of hundreds of ways"},{"time":245800,"text":"that men and women\nare unequal in our community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248840,"text":"The next thing we did\nwas build advocacy organizations."},{"time":252360,"text":"We tried to do things\nthat were unignorable,"},{"time":256320,"text":"like wearing pants to church\nand trying to attend all-male meetings."},{"time":261800,"text":"These seem like simple things,"},{"time":264320,"text":"but to us, the organizers,\nthey were enormously costly."},{"time":268560,"text":"We lost relationships. We lost jobs."},{"time":271840,"text":"We got hate mail on a daily basis."},{"time":273920,"text":"We were attacked in social media\nand national press."},{"time":277280,"text":"We received death threats."},{"time":279000,"text":"We lost standing in our community.\nSome of us got excommunicated."},{"time":283240,"text":"Most of us got put\nin front of a disciplinary council,"},{"time":286160,"text":"and were rejected\nfrom the communities that we loved"},{"time":289320,"text":"because we wanted to make them better,\nbecause we believed that they could be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294480,"text":"And I began to expect this reaction\nfrom my own people."},{"time":297760,"text":"I know what it feels like when you feel\nlike someone's trying to change you"},{"time":301720,"text":"or criticize you."},{"time":303760,"text":"But what utterly shocked me\nwas throughout all of this work"},{"time":307920,"text":"I received equal measures of vitriol\nfrom the secular left,"},{"time":313400,"text":"the same vehemence as the religious right."},{"time":317120,"text":"And what my secular friends didn't realize\nwas that this religious hostility,"},{"time":321000,"text":"these phrases of, \"Oh, all religious\npeople are crazy or stupid.\""},{"time":325160,"text":"\"Don't pay attention to religion.\""},{"time":327240,"text":"\"They're going to be\nhomophobic and sexist.\""},{"time":330600,"text":"What they didn't understand"},{"time":332680,"text":"was that that type of hostility\ndid not fight religious extremism,"},{"time":337280,"text":"it bred religious extremism."},{"time":340640,"text":"Those arguments don't work,\nand I know because I remember"},{"time":344080,"text":"someone telling me\nthat I was stupid for being Mormon."},{"time":349800,"text":"And what it caused me to do\nwas defend myself and my people"},{"time":353680,"text":"and everything we believe in,\nbecause we're not stupid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358720,"text":"So criticism and hostility doesn't work,\nand I didn't listen to these arguments."},{"time":363520,"text":"When I hear these arguments,\nI still continue to bristle,"},{"time":366240,"text":"because I have family and friends."},{"time":367920,"text":"These are my people,\nand I'm the first to defend them,"},{"time":370640,"text":"but the struggle is real."},{"time":372680,"text":"How do we respect\nsomeone's religious beliefs"},{"time":376480,"text":"while still holding them accountable\nfor the harm or damage"},{"time":379800,"text":"that those beliefs may cause others?"},{"time":382120,"text":"It's a tough question.\nI still don't have a perfect answer."},{"time":384920,"text":"My parents and I have been walking\non this tightrope for the last decade."},{"time":389080,"text":"They're intelligent people.\nThey're lovely people."},{"time":391840,"text":"And let me try to help you\nunderstand their perspective."},{"time":395760,"text":"In Mormonism, we believe\nthat after you die,"},{"time":398760,"text":"if you keep all the rules\nand you follow all the rituals,"},{"time":402120,"text":"you can be together as a family again."},{"time":405240,"text":"And to my parents,\nme doing something as simple"},{"time":407680,"text":"as having a sleeveless top right now,\nshowing my shoulders,"},{"time":411080,"text":"that makes me unworthy."},{"time":412880,"text":"I won't be with my family\nin the eternities."},{"time":416240,"text":"But even more, I had a brother\ndie in a tragic accident at 15,"},{"time":420440,"text":"and something as simple as this\nmeans we won't be together as a family."},{"time":424720,"text":"And to my parents, they cannot understand"},{"time":428320,"text":"why something as simple\nas fashion or women's rights"},{"time":431440,"text":"would prevent me\nfrom seeing my brother again."},{"time":434160,"text":"And that's the mindset\nthat we're dealing with,"},{"time":436920,"text":"and criticism does not change that."},{"time":440040,"text":"And so my parents and I\nhave been walking this tightrope,"},{"time":442760,"text":"explaining our sides,\nrespecting one another,"},{"time":445720,"text":"but actually invalidating\neach other's very basic beliefs"},{"time":449720,"text":"by the way we live our lives,\nand it's been difficult."},{"time":453080,"text":"The way that we've been able to do that"},{"time":455560,"text":"is to get past those defensive shells"},{"time":458000,"text":"and really see the soft inside\nof unbelief and belief"},{"time":462040,"text":"and try to respect each other\nwhile still holding boundaries clear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466680,"text":"The other thing that the secular left\nand the atheists and the orthodox"},{"time":471160,"text":"and the religious right,\nwhat they all don't understand"},{"time":475200,"text":"was why even care\nabout religious activism?"},{"time":478080,"text":"I cannot tell you the hundreds\nof people who have said,"},{"time":481160,"text":"\"If you don't like religion, just leave.\""},{"time":483800,"text":"Why would you try to change it?"},{"time":486880,"text":"Because what is taught on the Sabbath"},{"time":489342,"text":"leaks into our politics,\nour health policy,"},{"time":492400,"text":"violence around the world."},{"time":494280,"text":"It leaks into education,\nmilitary, fiscal decision-making."},{"time":498000,"text":"These laws get legally\nand culturally codified."},{"time":501320,"text":"In fact, my own religion has had\nan enormous effect on this nation."},{"time":506280,"text":"For example, during Prop 8,\nmy church raised over 22 million dollars"},{"time":510880,"text":"to fight same-sex marriage in California."},{"time":514840,"text":"Forty years ago,\npolitical historians will say,"},{"time":519080,"text":"that if it wasn't for the Mormon\nopposition to the Equal Rights Amendment,"},{"time":522960,"text":"we'd have an Equal Rights Amendment\nin our Constitution today."},{"time":526800,"text":"How many lives did that affect?"},{"time":530800,"text":"And we can spend time\nfighting every single one"},{"time":533600,"text":"of these little tiny laws and rules,"},{"time":536760,"text":"or we can ask ourselves,"},{"time":538360,"text":"why is gender inequality\nthe default around the world?"},{"time":544560,"text":"Why is that the assumption?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547240,"text":"Because religion doesn't just\ncreate the roots of morality,"},{"time":553200,"text":"it creates the seeds of normality."},{"time":557280,"text":"Religions can liberate or subjugate,"},{"time":560640,"text":"they can empower or exploit,\nthey can comfort or destroy,"},{"time":563880,"text":"and the people that tip the scales\nover to the ethical and the moral"},{"time":568440,"text":"are often not those in charge."},{"time":571600,"text":"Religions can't be dismissed or ignored."},{"time":574520,"text":"We need to take them seriously."},{"time":577440,"text":"But it's not easy to influence a religion,\nlike we just talked about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"But I'll tell you\nwhat my people have done."},{"time":584240,"text":"My groups are small,\nthere's hundreds of us,"},{"time":586360,"text":"but we've had huge impact."},{"time":588760,"text":"Right now, women's pictures\nare hanging in the halls next to men"},{"time":591800,"text":"for the first time."},{"time":593040,"text":"Women are now allowed\nto pray in our church-wide meetings,"},{"time":595800,"text":"and they never were before\nin the general conferences."},{"time":598840,"text":"As of last week, in a historic move,"},{"time":601400,"text":"three women were invited\ndown to three leadership boards"},{"time":604600,"text":"that oversee the entire church."},{"time":606600,"text":"We've seen perceptual shifts\nin the Mormon community"},{"time":609440,"text":"that allow for talk of gender inequality."},{"time":611960,"text":"We've opened up space,\nregardless of being despised,"},{"time":615360,"text":"for more conservative women\nto step in and make real changes,"},{"time":619280,"text":"and the words \"women\" and \"the priesthood\"\ncan now be uttered in the same sentence."},{"time":624160,"text":"I never had that."},{"time":626800,"text":"My daughter and my nieces are inheriting\na religion that I never had,"},{"time":631400,"text":"that's more equal -- we've had an effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635400,"text":"It wasn't easy standing in those lines"},{"time":638320,"text":"trying to get into those male meetings."},{"time":641520,"text":"There were hundreds of us,"},{"time":643720,"text":"and one by one, when we got to the door,"},{"time":646360,"text":"we were told, \"I'm sorry,\nthis meeting is just for men,\""},{"time":650040,"text":"and we had to step back\nand watch men get into the meeting"},{"time":654840,"text":"as young as 12 years old,"},{"time":657000,"text":"escorted and walked past us\nas we all stood in line."},{"time":661080,"text":"But not one woman in that line\nwill forget that day,"},{"time":663840,"text":"and not one little boy\nthat walked past us will forget that day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669520,"text":"If we were a multinational corporation\nor a government, and that had happened,"},{"time":675160,"text":"there would be outrage,"},{"time":676800,"text":"but we're just a religion."},{"time":679240,"text":"We're all just part of religions."},{"time":683120,"text":"We can't keep looking\nat religion that way,"},{"time":685880,"text":"because it doesn't only affect me,\nit affects my daughter"},{"time":688760,"text":"and all of your daughters\nand what opportunities they have,"},{"time":691760,"text":"what they can wear,\nwho they can love and marry,"},{"time":694038,"text":"if they have access\nto reproductive healthcare."},{"time":697160,"text":"We need to reclaim morality\nin a secular context"},{"time":700520,"text":"that creates ethical scrutiny\nand accountability"},{"time":702800,"text":"for religions all around the world,"},{"time":705000,"text":"but we need to do it in a respectful way"},{"time":708160,"text":"that breeds cooperation and not extremism."},{"time":711400,"text":"And we can do it through\nunignorable acts of bravery,"},{"time":715480,"text":"standing up for gender equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718840,"text":"It's time that half\nof the world's population"},{"time":721360,"text":"had voice and equality\nwithin our world's religions,"},{"time":724320,"text":"churches, synagogues, mosques\nand shrines around the world."},{"time":728880,"text":"I'm working on my people.\nWhat are you doing for yours?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":733400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}